<subSubSection id="C3246572FFE9C946FF62FAD4FACDF9B6" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFE9C946FF62FAD4FACDF9B6" blockId="72.[151,1437,1230,2013]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FF62FAD4FECCFABB" bold="true" box="[199,322,1374,1400]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFE9C946FE0AFAD5FD91FABA" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[431,543,1375,1401]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaciba" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FE0AFAD5FD91FABA" box="[431,543,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. yaciba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FD81FAD5FD18FABA" bold="true" box="[548,662,1375,1401]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFE9C946FD81FAD5FD18FABA" box="[548,662,1375,1401]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFE9C946FCC3FAD5FC74FABB" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[870,1018,1375,1400]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FCC3FAD5FC74FABB" box="[870,1018,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FBADFAD5FB2DFABA" box="[1032,1187,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 221–224" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,1054,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-312@56.[160,1427,1043,1895]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 221–224. Meri pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov., male (IBSP 20795), left palp (221 prolateral, 222 ventral, 223 retrolateral, 224 detail of embolus). C—conductor; E—embolus; mr—membranous region; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RTA— retrolateral tibial apophysis; SdP—subdistal projection; tp—tegular protrusion; vb—ventral branch of RTA. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550350/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 221–224</figureCitation>
) by the palp with RTA with a ventral branch (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FE37FA09FE7DFA5E" box="[402,499,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 298</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from the latter species by RTA distally pointed with ventral branch roughly three times longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FD03FA2DFCCFFA02" box="[678,833,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–291" captionStartId="70.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[165,1415,317,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-93@70.[155,1432,309,1769]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURES 285–291. Meri vanini spec. nov. 285–288 male (MPEG 30859, paratype), left palp (285 prolateral, 286 ventral, 287 retrolateral, 288 detail of embolus, ventral); 289–291 female (MZSP 37241, paratype) (289 epigyne, 290 vulva, 291 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum; tp—tegular protrusion. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550516/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 288–289</figureCitation>
) and embolus with subdistal projection hook-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FF05FA41FE8EFA26" box="[160,256,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 300</figureCitation>
) (RTA distally blunt with ventral branch triangular, slightly longer than wide and embolus with subdistal projection long, mediad and laminar in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFE9C946FDFDFA65FD60F9CB" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[600,750,1519,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FDFDFA65FD60F9CB" box="[600,750,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFE9C946FB9EFA65FB5FF9CB" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1083,1233,1519,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FB9EFA65FB5FF9CB" box="[1083,1233,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FB7CFA65FAD5F9CA" bold="true" box="[1241,1371,1519,1545]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFE9C946FB7CFA65FAD5F9CA" box="[1241,1371,1519,1545]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FACFFA65FF75F9EE" captionStart="FIGURES 225–230" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1364,1388]" captionTargetBox="[228,1355,464,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-168@57.[221,1366,453,1341]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 225–230. Meri pictitarsis (Simon) comb. nov. 225–227 female (MNHN 1140, syntype) (225 epigyne, 226 vulva, 227 schematic course of internal duct system); 228–230 female (MNHN 1140, syntype) (228 epigyne, 229 vulva, 230 schematic course of internal duct system). EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550352/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 225–227</figureCitation>
) by the epigyne with MS widest anteriorly, partly covering LL and EP triangular. They are distinguished by the MS with posterior margin anterior to that of LL and EP more than 1.5 times longer than wide (MS with posterior margins in line with posterior margin of LL and EP slightly longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFE9C946FBB3F9D1FB22F9B7" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1046,1196,1627,1652]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictitarsis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FBB3F9D1FB22F9B7" box="[1046,1196,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">M. pictitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FB16F9D1FABDF9B6" bold="true" box="[1203,1331,1627,1653]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFE9C946FB16F9D1FABDF9B6" box="[1203,1331,1627,1653]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFE9C947FF62F9F4FF5CFF16" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFE9C946FF62F9F4FA83F88D" blockId="72.[151,1437,1230,2013]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FF62F9F4FDABF95B" bold="true" box="[199,549,1662,1689]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFE9C946FE0FF9F4FD96F95B" box="[426,536,1662,1688]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 11.7. Prosoma 5.2 long, 4.5 wide. Opisthosoma 6.0 long, 3.0 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.46, 0.40, 0.30, 0.35; interdistances: 0.20, 0.05, 0.45, 0.45, 0.27, 0.18. Legs: I: 29.9 (8.0, 2.9, 8.4, 8.4, 2.2); II: 32.3 (9.0, 2.9, 9.2, 8.9, 2.3); III: 21.5 (6.2, 2.2, 5.9, 5.5, 1.7); IV: 7.7, 2.1, 6.8, 6.9, 2.0). Palp: PTA trapezoid, roughly 2 times wider than long; RTA roughly 1.5 times longer than wide; cymbium with small retroproximal projection; subtegulum visible betwee 9–11:30 o’clock in ventral view; tegulum depressed close to conductor; conductor roughly the same width throughout; embolus curving subdistally (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FC54F8B9FB01F88E" box="[1009,1167,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 297–300</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FB3FF8B9FA8FF88D" box="[1178,1281,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 304–308" captionStartId="74.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1396,201,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-23@74.[176,1411,181,1929]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 304–308. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 304–306 male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (304 prolateral, 305 ventral, 306 retrolateral); 307–308 female (AMNH, paratype) (307 epigyne, 308 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550522/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">304–306</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFE9C947FF62F8DDFF5CFF16" blockId="72.[151,1437,1230,2013]" lastBlockId="73.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFE9C946FF62F8DDFE20F8B3" bold="true" box="[199,430,1878,1905]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFE9C946FE8AF8DCFE2FF8B3" box="[303,417,1878,1904]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Prosoma 6.0 long, 5.2 wide. Opisthosoma destroyed. Eyes: diameters: 0.50, 0.40, 0.30, 0.38; interdistances: 0.30, 0.30, 0.70, 0.61, 0.30, 0.25. Legs: I: 26.1 (7.2, 3.0, 7.0, 6.9, 2.0); II: 29.0 (8.0, 3.1, 8.0, 7.9, 2.0); III: 20.3 (6.0, 2.6, 5.0, 5.1, 1.6); IV: absent. Epigyne (broken anteriorly): MS as wide as long with lateral margins diverging anteriorly; HP triangular, opening at posterior margin of MS (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FC59F849FBECF81E" box="[1020,1122,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs 301</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE9C946FBCAF849FB13F81E" box="[1135,1181,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 304–308" captionStartId="74.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1396,201,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-23@74.[176,1411,181,1929]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 304–308. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 304–306 male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (304 prolateral, 305 ventral, 306 retrolateral); 307–308 female (AMNH, paratype) (307 epigyne, 308 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550522/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">307</figureCitation>
). Vulva: internal ducts with FW C-shaped, mediad; GP longer than wide, antero mediad; SP rounded; FD antero mediad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE8C947FB5CFF1DFA16FF72" box="[1273,1432,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 297–303" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1708,1732]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,292,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-44@73.[154,1433,273,1684]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 297–303. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 297–300 male (AMNH), left palp (297 prolateral, 298 ventral, 299 retrolateral, 300 detail of embolus); 301–303 female (AMNH) (301 epigyne, 302 vulva, 303 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; mr—membranous region; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial projection; SdP—subdistal projection; SP—spermathecae; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550520" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550520/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Figs 302–303</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFE8C947FF32FF31FF4BFF16" box="[151,197,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 304–308" captionStartId="74.[151,264,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[196,1396,201,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-23@74.[176,1411,181,1929]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 304–308. Meri yaciba spec. nov. 304–306 male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (304 prolateral, 305 ventral, 306 retrolateral); 307–308 female (AMNH, paratype) (307 epigyne, 308 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550522" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550522/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">308</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
